SIMPLE: recommence
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Recommence
<hw>Re`com*mence"</hw> <pr>(r?`k?m*m?ns")</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To commence or begin again.</def>
<rj><au>Howell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To begin anew to be; to act again as.</def>
<mark>[Archaic.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He seems desirous enough of <qex>recommencing</qex> courtier.</q>
<rj><qau>Johnson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Recommence</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Recommence
<hw>Re`com*mence"</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Pref. <ets>re-</ets> +
<ets>commence</ets>: cf. F. <ets>recommencer</ets>.]</ety> <def>To
commence again or anew.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Recommencement</ent>⟦br⟧
